rComments: Professor Validashti is the best math professor I have had thus far in my engineering workload. He is funny and easy to understand, and he genuinely cares about his students. Very good teacher, highly recommend him!
Great class! Great professor who is funny and very nice!!I enjoyed his class!!

This class is enough of a challenge so that I'm not bored, but is easy enough to where it doesn't cause too much extra stress in my life. Validashti is an awesome professor and I'm so happy I am taking MATH415 in his class and not in a different professor's class.
The professor has natural sense of humor, and his delivery of the lecture is awesome! Easy explanations, good examples. I really like attending this class even if it is not mandatory.

Favorite math instructor I've ever had. Though I have a very limited interest in Linear Algebra, I found the class consistently engaging. He makes great effort to impart true understanding of the material in the most accessible manner, but at the same time doesn't take himself too seriously. Going to class is crucial, but if you do, an A is easy.

Dude is a great teacher to have for a course like Math 415. He's willing to help and takes the time to make sure his students understand the concepts. Makes lectures fun with his natural charm and sense on humor.
Awesome professor! Goes through concepts thoroughly and really helps you understand the material.

Javid is one of the best professors in UIUC. Difference from other professors is that he explains all concepts using examples. Because of that, I have understood the concepts easily. Grading system is fair, which is 4time exams (15pts each) and homework (40pts). If you are in the entire lecture, you can definitely get good grade :)
Javid is a really helpful and clear teacher. His lecture notes are helpful and he doesn't try to trick students. He definitely keeps the class laughing and the exams and homework are very fair.
Javid is easily one of the best professors I have ever had.  He is VERY easy to talk to, simply a nice person and just a fantastic teacher overall.  If you can take a class with him...DO IT!

Great professor! Explains concepts in class very clearly and cracks a joke or two just to make sure everyone is still interested. He is also very understanding and helpful during special circumstances.
Greatest math class I had so far for 4yrs of school. He is very nice and willing to help students and explain stuffs very well. Take his class he is the best.
Homework is worth 40% of the grade and there is quite a bit of extra credit. Even though the class is easy, you learn a lot because he focuses on the basics before moving ahead.

Weekly homework assignments,worth 40% of final grade, are sometimes gone over before the assignment is due. Exams are based off of the textbook review. Provides review sessions for exams. While he isn't the best teacher, he is understanding. Total comprehension of material isn't emphasized so the class is easy.

One of the best professors I've had at this university. Willing to help students, unlike some teachers who live to make their students' lives miserable. His reviews are very helpful and grading is fair. Good sense of humor.

As others have said, he is a great professor and the class is easy. This combination actually is perfect for learning the material if you try. He does move pretty quickly in class, but he's more than willing to answer questions. I think he's funny as well =)

This professor is the easiest possible Linear Algebra Professor. Anyone who didn't give him a 5 on easiness is flat out lying. This is a professor who will teach you nothing if that's what you want. You do not need to learn anything to pass with an A. However, this does not mean that he isn't a great professor. He can teach you A LOT if YOU try.

Lectures are clear and comprehensive and notes will be extremely helpful when doing homework and studying for exams. Only criticism would be that he tends to lecture pretty quickly so it can be difficult to catch up if you fall behind with your notes. But this is a minor issue, and you definitely won't regret having him as a professor. He's great.
He is a good teacher and he has fun in class. If you show up and pay attention you should get an A. His reviews are the most helpful reviews ever.
The class is very interesting, give it time to grow on you. The professor is superb, and also try reading the textbook it helps a lot.
